Sure, here are some examples:

1. *Lak* zadatak je bio da ispečem kolač. (*Easy* task was to bake a cake.)
2. Ljubičasta boja je *lak*a za oči. (Purple color is *easy* on the eyes.)
3. On je *lak* na rečima, ali teško se drži obećanja. (He's *light* on words, but he's hard to keep his promises.)
4. Ova torba je veoma *lak*a za nošenje. (This bag is very *light* to carry.)
5. Potrebno mi je nešto *lak*še za večeru jer ne mogu da pojedem tešku hranu. (I need something *light* for dinner because I can't eat heavy food.)
6. Njen glas je tako *lak* da zvuči poput ptice. (Her voice is so *light* that it sounds like a bird.)
7. Ovaj materijal je *lak*ši za održavanje od drugih. (This material is *easier* to maintain than others.)
8. *Lak*o je videti da je on umoran. (*It's easy* to see that he's tired.)
9. Ovaj zadatak je *lak*ši od prethodnog. (This task is *easier* than the previous one.)
10. Mleko je dobar izvor *lak*toze. (Milk is a good source of *lactose*.)

Note: The word "lak" has multiple meanings in Serbian, and I have provided translations for each example to make it clear which meaning is being used in each case.